hire, Skotland, United Kingdom","of Polkelly, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Skotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Skotland, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1440–1507":"1440–1507","1444–1509":"1444–1509","1460–1558":"1460–1558","1460–Male":"1460–Overleden","1489–Female":"1489–Overleden","1415–Male":"1415–Overleden","1426–1455":"1426–1455","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","23 Oct 1455":"23 oktober 1455","1426":"1426","1415":"1415","1558":"1558","Abt 1491":"circa 1491","1489":"1489","1455":"1455","1444":"1444","about 1489":"circa 1489","1509":"1509","1507":"1507","about 1460":"circa 1460","of, Polkelly, Ayr, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Gadgirth, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Gadgirth, Ayrshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","of Polkelly, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Schotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1440–1507":"1440–1507","1444–1509":"1444–1509","1460–1558":"1460–1558","1460–Male":"1460–Deceased","1489–Female":"1489–Deceased","1415–Male":"1415–Deceased","1426–1455":"1426–1455","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","23 Oct 1455":"23 October 1455","1426":"1426","1415":"1415","1558":"1558","Abt 1491":"about 1491","1489":"1489","1455":"1455","1444":"1444","about 1489":"about 1489","1509":"1509","1507":"1507","about 1460":"about 1460","of, Polkelly, Ayr, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Gadgirth, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Gadgirth, Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","of Polkelly, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Chalmers","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: from Older Scots <i>chalmer</i> ‘chamberlain’; compare   Chambers  . The <i>mb</i> was assimilated to <i>mm</i>; the <i>l</i> was purely graphic, indicating that the preceding <i>a</i> was long.","English: possibly a localized form of <b>Challinor</b> (see   Challender  ), with dissimilation of <i>ln</i> to <i>lm</i> in <i>Chalner</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Chambers","meanings":["English:","from Middle English <i>chaumbre</i> ‘room (in a house); reception room in a palace or official building’ (Old French <i>chambre</i>). It is identical in implied function with the   Chamberlain  , which denoted an official: to pay <i>in cameram</i> was to pay into the exchequer, of which the <i>camerarius</i> or chamberer was in charge. The surname also applied to clerks employed there. As the office of <i>Chamberlain</i> rose in the social scale, this term remained reserved for more humble servants of the bedchamber or private quarters.","(of Norman origin): habitational name from Les Chambres, Manche (France)."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Chalmers of Gadgirth was born in 1440, in Gadgirth, Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, John Chalmers Of Gadgirth, was 26 and his mother, Lady Elizabeth Hamilton, was 14. He married Marion Hay about 1491, in Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1507, in his hometown, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1440–1507":"1440–1507","1444–1509":"1444–1509","1460–1558":"1460–1558","1460–Male":"1460–Surnud","1489–Female":"1489–Surnud","1415–Male":"1415–Surnud","1426–1455":"1426–1455","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","23 Oct 1455":"23. oktoober 1455","1426":"1426","1415":"1415","1558":"1558","Abt 1491":"umbes 1491","1489":"1489","1455":"1455","1444":"1444","about 1489":"umbes 1489","1509":"1509","1507":"1507","about 1460":"umbes 1460","of, Polkelly, Ayr, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Gadgirth, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Gadgirth, Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","of Polkelly, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1440–1507":"1440–1507","1444–1509":"1444–1509","1